## What I changed

I treated the Fresh Eyes notes as a strong but not-binding list, verified every new fact by web search, then made five edits:

**Added substance (the high-value gaps):**
- **SNL** — new paragraph in the cast section. Goodman hosted *Saturday Night Live* 13 times (1989–2013), third-most ever behind Steve Martin and Alec Baldwin, with the "Platinum Lounge" inside joke. This was the one real reader-expectation gap, and it's the cleanest proof of the thesis: a 9 returning year after year to a *family that was never even his show*, just to be useful in the room.
- **No Oscar nomination, ever** — added to the "underestimated craftsman" beat. The everyman overlooked even by the people whose job is to notice. Thesis at its sharpest.
- **Fatherhood payoff** — the fatherless boy became a present father, and his 2021 line crediting Molly's character to "her mother and her grandmother" is a perfect 9 deflection. It cashes the opening shaving-mirror wound.

**Trimmed the tics:**
- Cut the duplicate "nothing to the party" (kept the stronger diagnosis-section instance).
- Varied one of three stacked "Not X. Not Y." negation beats so the rhythm doesn't read as a tic.

**Rejected one note:** I left the 2018 Roseanne-tweet beat where it is. Fresh-eyes wanted "a hair more air," but it's already a full standalone paragraph; breaking it out further would over-weight a sub-beat against the drinking and SNL material.

